From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0006/N] bytes_bsd_aarch64.hpp: add FreeBSD branch using <sys/endian.h>

The file only handled `__APPLE__` (Darwin uses libkern/OSByteOrder.h)
and fell through to `#error "Unimplemented"` for FreeBSD. CheriBSD on
Morello ends up in the FreeBSD branch.

FreeBSD's `<sys/endian.h>` exposes `__bswap16`, `__bswap32`, `__bswap64`
as inline functions. Define `bswap_*` to those so the existing
`Bytes::swap_u*` definitions further down the file keep working
unchanged.

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0006)

--- a/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/bytes_bsd_aarch64.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/os_cpu/bsd_aarch64/bytes_bsd_aarch64.hpp
@@ -31,10 +31,18 @@
 #include <libkern/OSByteOrder.h>
 #endif

+#if defined(__FreeBSD__)
+#include <sys/endian.h>
+#endif
+
 #if defined(__APPLE__)
 #  define bswap_16(x) OSSwapInt16(x)
 #  define bswap_32(x) OSSwapInt32(x)
 #  define bswap_64(x) OSSwapInt64(x)
+#elif defined(__FreeBSD__)
+#  define bswap_16(x) __bswap16(x)
+#  define bswap_32(x) __bswap32(x)
+#  define bswap_64(x) __bswap64(x)
 #else
 #  error "Unimplemented"
 #endif
